%26quot%3B%20its%20security%20protocols.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECiti%20told%20New%20York-based%20employees%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20the%20firm%20had%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20the%20security%20presence%20and%20capabilities%20at%20our%20headquarters%26quot%3B%20within%20the%20past%20year.%20%26quot%3BThis%20includes%20working%20closely%20with%20the%20NYPD%2C%26quot%3B%20Ed%20Skyler%2C%20Citi's%20head%20of%20enterprise%20services%20and%20public%20affairs%2C%20said%20in%20a%20memo%20to%20staff.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20feel%20confident%20with%20the%20protocols%20we%20have%20in%20place%2C%20we%20will%20not%20hesitate%20to%20adjust%20if%20necessary%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20companies%20seeking%20to%20boost%20security%2C%20the%20extra%20layer%20of%20protection%20won't%20come%20cheap.%20Two%20security%20executives%20in%20New%20York%20City%20say%20posting%20an%20armed%20former%20or%20off-duty%20police%20officer%20in%20your%20lobby%20will%20cost%20building%20managers%20%2475%20to%20%24200%20an%20hour%20or%20more.%20Hiring%20an%20armed%20escort%20to%20protect%20a%20CEO%20or%20other%20prominent%20person%20will%20cost%20in%20the%20%24135%20to%20%24200%20range%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20it's%20not%20denting%20demand.%20Herman%20Weisberg%20said%20his%20security%20company%20usually%20hires%20about%2015%20armed%20former%20military%20and%20NYPD%20officers%20to%20protect%20CEOs%20and%20other%20high-profile%20individuals%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20On%20Tuesday%2C%20that%20number%20was%20up%20to%2030%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20SAGE%20Intelligence%20thinks%20it%20will%20grow%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeisberg%2C%20a%20former%20NYPD%20detective%2C%20said%20he%20is%20also%20seeing%20an%20increase%20in%20requests%20from%20companies%20for%20%26quot%3Bthreat%20assessments%2C%26quot%3B%20including%20risks%20tied%20to%20former%20disgruntled%20ex-employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20firm%20wants%20us%20to%20work