outh%20India%2C%20the%20Eri%20tank%20system%20is%20predominantly%20practised%20in%20parts%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-4-1648035254.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-4-1648035254-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-4-1648035254-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-4-1648035254-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Fwater-4-1648035254-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-280164%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKolavai%20lake%20where%20Chengalpattu%20Eri%20is%20located.%20Picture%20Credits%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3AChengalpat_lake.jpg%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWikipedia%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20traditional%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F394956%2Findia-pond-man-ramveer-tanwar-revives-ponds-filled-with-garbage-waste%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewater%20management%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20South%20India%2C%20the%20Eri%20tank%20system%20is%20predominantly%20practised%20in%20parts%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Almost%20one-third%20of%20the%20total%20irrigated%20area%20in%20the%20state%20is%20watered%20by%20the%20Eri%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20oldest%20water%20management%20systems%20in%20India%2C%20it%20acts%20as%20a%20flood-control%20system%20that%20also%20prevents%20soil%20erosion%20and%20runoff%20water%20wastage%2C%20especially%20during%20heavy%20rainfall%2C%20which%20is%20a%20recurring%20occurrence%20in%20the%20present%20times.%20Additionally%2C%20Eris%20also%20recharges%20groundwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20essentially%20two%20types%20of%20Eris%2C%20one%20that%20is%20system%20Eri%2C%20fed%20by%20channels%20to%20divert%20river%20water%2C%20or%20the%20other%20being%20non-system%20one%20which%20is%20entirely%20fed%20by%20rain.%20These%20tanks%20are%20all%20interconnected%20and%20enable%20access%20of%20water%20to%20the%20farthest%20of%20villages%2C%20thus%20maintaining%20a%20balance%20in%20the%20water%20level%2C%20in%20case%20of%20excess%20supply%20through%20floods.%20This%20system%20allows%20for%20a%20sustainable%20solution%20to%20use%20the%20river%20water%20for%20cultivation%20and%20without%20it%2C%20paddy%20cultivation%20in%20the%20state%20would%20have%20been%20impossible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20Indus%20Valley%20Civilisation%2C%20Chanakya%E2%80%99s%20Arthashastra%20that%20mention%20water%20harvesting%20systems%20to%20the%20Grand%20Anicut%20of%20Kallanai%20built%20across%20river%20Cauvery%20by%20the%20Chola%20king%20Karikala%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20countless%20successful%20examples%20of%20water%20conservation%20methods%20all%20across%20the%20pages%20of%20history.%20All%20one%20needs%20to%20do%20is%20to%20take%20initiative%2C%20look%20back%2C%20learn%20and%20re-create%20sustainable%20solutions%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Yoshita%20Rao%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753803000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FE23IxHYVoAEKCoA-1753800077.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D477810%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Almost%20every%20region%20in%20India%20is%20blessed%20with%20its%20own%20water%20management%20methods%20that%20were%20tailored%20to%20fit%20the%20unique%20geographical%20and%20cultural%20needs%20of%20the%20place%20and%20the%20community.%20Here%20are%20some%20of%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Ananya%20Barua%22%2C%22e