rd%20Pritchard%20Gee%2C%20who%20lived%20and%20worked%20in%20Assam%2C%20articulated%20his%20observations%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wildlife%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1964)%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20early%201930s%2C%20Kaziranga%20was%20a%20closed%20book%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20%3Cem%3Eterra%20incognita%3C%2Fem%3E%20(unknown%20land)%20completely%20left%20to%20itself%20by%20the%20Forest%20Department.%20I%20remember%20trying%20to%20get%20permission%20to%20go%20there%20in%201934%2C%20but%20the%20rather%20lame%20excuse%20of%20the%20British%20D.F.O.%20was%2C%20%E2%80%98No%20one%20can%20enter%20the%20place.%20It%20is%20all%20swamps%20and%20leeches%2C%20and%20even%20elephants%20cannot%20go%20there.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20Kaziranga%E2%80%99s%20current%20avatar%20would%20surprise%20Gee.%20It%E2%80%99s%20spinning%20a%20success%20story%20across%20430%20sq%20km%2C%20playing%20host%20to%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20population%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F454940%2Fkaziranga-drones-protecting-rhinos%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eendangered%20Indian%20one-horned%20rhinoceros%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20swamp%20deer%2C%20large%20elephants%2C%20and%20a%20high%20density%20of%20tigers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20today%20is%20a%20UNESCO-approved%20verdant%20sprawl%20looked%20quite%20the%20opposite%20a%20century%20ago.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20man%20behind%20the%20makeover%20is%20Mahi%20Chandra%20Miri%2C%20whose%20story%20will%20remain%20a%20page-turner%20in%20the%20annals%20of%20conservation%20history.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20life%20and%20times%20of%20Mahi%20Miri%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20wooden%20signboard%20five%20kilometres%20east%20of%20the%20Bagori%20sub-beat%20forest%20office%20at%20the%20Kaziranga%20National%20Park%20reads%20in%20bold%20font%2C%20%E2%80%98Mahi%20Miri%20Tower%E2%80%99.%20An%20arrow%20directs%20you%20to%20a%20hillock%2C%20where%20the%20conservationist%20spent%20many%20an%20evening%20keeping%20watch%20on%20the%20forested%20land%20(in%20those%20days%2C%20its%20identity%20was%20that%20of%20a%20game%20sanctuary).%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20vantage%20point%20offered%20him%20sweeping%20views%20of%20the%20forest%3B%20he%E2%80%99d%20be%20quick%20to%20notice%20any%20skulduggery%3B%20the%20sanctuary%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F463429%2Fandaman-24x7-forest-station-wildlife-crime-deer-wild-pigs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enotorious%20for%20poaching%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-1753698110.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kaziranga%20National%20Park%20was%20once%20a%20game%20sanctuary%20notorious%20for%20poaching%20activities%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-1753698110.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-1753698110-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-1753698110-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-1753698110-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2Fjamtara-wilderness-camp-1753698110-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-477201%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKaziranga%20National%20Park%20was%20once%20a%20game%20sanctuary%20notorious%20for%20poaching%20activities.%20Picture%20source%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FC4YGhuVv9QC%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPushkar%20NS%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20would%20commence%20his%20vigil%20at%20dawn%2C%20binoculars%20trained%20unwaveringly%20on%20the%20land%20beyond.%20And%20god%20forbid%20he%20spotted%20the%20miscreants%2C%20he%E2%80%99d%20rush%20on%20elephant%20back%20to%20catch%20them.%20The%20hillock%20was%20christened%20after%20him%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20long%20after%20he%20passed%20away%20in%201939%20at%20the%20age%20of%2036.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20stands%20tall%2C%20an%20ode%20to%20a%20hefty%20legacy%20he%20left%20behind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20love%20for%20animals%20was%20well-known%2C%20shares%20his%20great-nephew%20Tridip%20Patir%3B%20his%20bonds%20with%20them%20were%20instinctive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201903%2C%20Mahi%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F360895%2Fvivek-menon-wildlife-trust-of-india-wildlife-conservation-anti-poaching-elephant-corridors%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epenchant%20for%20nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20developed%20in%20his%20home%20village%2C%20Alimur%2C%20in%20Assam%E2%80%99s%20Lakhimpur.%20His%20discipline%20came%20from%20his%20father%2C%20Doley%20Miri%2C%20a%20man%20respected%20by%20the%20community.%20His%20beginnings%20were%20humble%3B%20Mahi%20and%20his%20brother%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20makeshift%20thatched%20cottage%20on%20a%20plot%20of%20hired%20land%20at%20Sivasagar.%20The%20boys%20attended%20the%20Sivasagar%20Town%20Government%20HE%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20tennis%20aficionado%2C%20Mahi%20often%20played%20legendary%20sportsman%20Prof%20PC%20Roy.%20He%20was%20hardworking%3B%20%E2%80%9Csoft-spoken%20and%20disciplined%E2%80%9D%20is%20how%20most%20described%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20was%20known%20for%20wearing%20his%20passion%20on%20his%20sleeve%2C%20at%20least%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20those%20who%20knew%20him%20well%20recall.%20Tridip%2C%20while%20looking%20to%20pursue%20his%20doctoral%20thesis%20in%20human-nature%20relationships%2C%20took%20a%20trip%20down%20memory%20lane%2C%20only%20to%20realise%20that%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20topic%20was%20impossible%20without%20learning%20more%20about%20his%20exemplar%20great-uncle.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20many%20in%20Assam%20are%20familiar%20with%20his%20wife%2C%20the%20celebrated%20Padma%20Shri%20educationist%20Indira%20Miri%2C%20few%20know%20about%20Mahi%20Chandra%20Miri%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20unfortunate%20because%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F467900%2Findian-wildlife-conservation-heroes-turtles-tigers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtributions%20to%20conservation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20his%20role%20in%20establishing%20Kaziranga%E2%80%99s%20protected%20status%20were%20immense.%20He%20was%20instrumental%20in%20transforming%20Kaziranga%20from%20a%20neglected%20wilderness%20into%20a%20world-renowned%20conservation%20landmark%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tridip%20remarks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaziranga%20has%20had%20quite%20a%20chequered%20journey.%20It%20was%20Mary%20Curzon%2C%20Lord%20Curzon%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20whose%20interventions%20helped%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20reserve%20forest%20in%201905%2C%20when%20she%20failed%20to%20see%20any%20rhinoceros%20on%20her%20trip%20to%20the%20park.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hoof%20marks%20in%20the%20forest%20did%20nothing%20to%20improve%20her%20mood.%20It%20was%20Balaram%20Hazarika%2C%20an%20eponymous%20animal%20tracker%20from%20Assam%2C%20who%20emphasised%20the%20urgent%20requirement%20for%20wildlife%20conservation%20to%20Mrs%20Curzon%2C%20who%20asked%20her%20husband%20to%20do%20something.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%201%20June%201905%20Kaziranga%20Proposed%20Reserve%20Forest%20was%20created.%20But%20by%201938%2C%20its%20existence%20was%20threatened%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F469442%2Fprofessor-rajib-tariang-empowers-assam-hunting-community-to-become-protectors-of-wildlife-promotes-eco-tourism%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erampant%20hunting%20activities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20a%20shadow%20of%20its%20current%20self.%20Tridip%20credits%20his%20great-uncle%20for%20the%20real%20on-ground%20transformation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inflection%20point%20in%20Mahi%E2%80%99s%20life%20came%20in%201929%2C%20when%20he%2C%20along%20with%20officer%20Madhab%20Bhattacharjee%2C%20was%20selected%20for%20the%20Imperial%20Forest%20Service.%20The%20duo%20was%20sent%20to%20Rangoon%20for%20training%20in%20the%20Forest%20College%20there.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20posting%20in%20Guwahati%20as%20an%20Extra%20Assistant%20Conservator%20of%20Forest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20man%20who%20put%20Kaziranga%20on%20the%20world%20map%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201930s%2C%20Kaziranga%20was%20infamous%20for%20poaching.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEP%20Gee%E2%80%99s%20book%20adds%20weight%20to%20the%20argument%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20talked%20to%20the%20Forest%20Officer%20who%20was%20the%20first%20to%20be%20deputed%20to%20survey%20Kaziranga%20in%20the%20mid-1930s.%20He%20found%20poachers%E2%80%99%20camps%20at%20every%20%3Cem%3Ebheel%3C%2Fem%3E%20(small%20lake)%2C%20and%20about%20forty%20carcasses%20of%20rhino%20with%20the%20horns%20removed.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20elaborates%20that%20the%20Mikirs%2C%20%E2%80%9Csimple%2C%20peaceful%20but%20very%20interesting%20tribal%20folk%20who%20dwell%20in%20the%20Mikir%20Hills%20just%20on%20the%20southern%20boundary%20of%20the%20sanctuary%E2%80%9D%2C%20were%20among%20the%20many%20po