ght%20to%20help%20them%2C%20providing%20them%20with%20the%20wherewithal%20to%20study%20and%20dream.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20reflected%20in%20his%20representing%20tribal%20communities%20at%20the%20Simon%20Commission%20in%20Shillong%20in%201929%2C%20led%20by%20Rai%20Saheb%20Sonadhar%20Senapati%2C%20who%20would%20become%20so%20impressed%20with%20Mahi%20that%20he%E2%80%99d%20give%20him%20his%20daughter%20Indira%E2%80%99s%20hand%20in%20marriage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20autobiography%2C%20Indira%20commends%20her%20husband%20for%20the%20respect%20he%20accorded%20to%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20my%20apprehensions%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20baseless%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20refers%20to%20her%20qualms%20before%20marriage.%20Her%20book%20details%20vivid%20memories%20of%20their%20time%20together%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20enjoyable%20for%20her%20being%20in%201934%20when%20Mahi%20was%20transferred%20to%20the%20Bagari%20range%20of%20the%20(then)%20Kaziranga%20game%20sanctuary%20with%20headquarters%20at%20Golaghat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F239958%2Fassam-manas-national-park-former-poachers-turn-forest-protectors-rhino-conservation-india-inspiring%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efocused%20on%20curbing%20poaching%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Indira%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20took%20advantage%20of%20the%20time%20to%20familiarise%20herself%20with%20the%20lay%20of%20the%20land.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20night%2C%20wild%20elephants%20raided%20the%20paddy%20fields%20to%20gorge%20on%20the%20ripe%20paddy.%20Occasionally%2C%20one%20of%20them%20would%20venture%20into%20the%20bungalow%20and%20noisily%20scratch%20its%20neck%20on%20one%20of%20the%20wooden%20posts%20supporting%20the%20building.%20I%20was%20too%20afraid%20to%20be%20able%20to%20sleep.%20The%20first%20couple%20of%20months%20in%20Baguri%2C%20I%20lived%20in%20constant%20fear%20of%20the%20forest%20and%20its%20wild%20beasts.%20But%2C%20slowly%2C%20I%20grew%20to%20love%20the%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCy3KL4oPmw9%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCy3KL4oPmw9%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCy3KL4oPmw9%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20SACHIN%20BHARALI%20(%40sachin_bharali)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20became%20accustomed%20to%20birds%20breaking%20the%20morning%20silence%20and%20silver%20fish%20disrupting%20the%20water%E2%80%99s%20surface.%20She%20took%20it%20all%20in.%20But%20what%20she%20most%20looked%20forward%20to%20was%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20interactions%20with%20the%20communities.%20His%20zeal%20snapped%20awake%20a%20devotion%20in%20them%20to%20protect%20their%20forests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVillagers%20began%20alerting%20him%20to%20the%20movement%20of%20poachers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20the%20communities%20become%20a%20part%20of%20his%20efforts%20helped%20Mahi.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20these%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F255198%2Fodisha-women-tribal-system-kodarapalli-thengapalli-forest-protection-environment-natural-resources-over-exploitation-guard-conservation-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarginalised%20tribes%20who%20had%20historically%20depended%20on%20the%20forests%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20their%20livelihood.%20As%20historian%20Arupjyoti%20Saikia%20points%20out%20in%20%3Cem%3EForests%20and%20Ecological%20History%20of%20Assam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CEveryday%20requirements%2C%20namely%2C%20grazing%2C%20shifting%20cultivation%2C%20collection%20of%20firewood%2C%20or%20fishing%20inside%20the%20forests%E2%80%A6the%20peasants%20collected%20fish%2C%20mostly%20as%20their%20daily%20food%20requirements%20and%20also%20for%20their%20petty%20trade%20with%20the%20help%20of%20locally%20developed%20traps%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20through%20dialogue%2C%20Mahi%20sparked%20change%20in%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Mising%20activist%20Doley%20shared%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3ERoundglass%20Sustain%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CMiri%20had%20the%20advantage%20of%20being%20a%20Mising%20tribesman%20and%20thus%20was%20in%20a%20position%20to%20empathise%20with%20the%20tribes%20in%20Kaziranga.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETogether%20with%20A%20J%20Milroy%2C%20the%20erstwhile%20conservator%20of%20the%20Assam%20Forest%20Department%2C%20he%20blazed%20a%20trail%20to%20amp%20up%20efforts%20to%20stop%20poaching.%20Their%20efforts%20culminated%20in%20Kaziranga%20being%20opened%20to%20visitors%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%201938.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20also%20supervised%20the%20capture%20of%20the%20first%20live%20rhino%20in%20Kaziranga%2C%20which%20was%20later%20sent%20to%20a%20zoo%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20As%20Tridip%20shares%2C%20when%20waters%20inundated%20the%20Karbi-Anglong%20area%20in%20Assam%20in%201939%2C%20Mahi%20chose%20to%20stay%20back%20and%20assist%20the%20locals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20also%20how%20he%20contracted%20Black%20Fever%2C%20which%20later%20took%20his%20life%20at%20the%20young%20age%20of%2036%20in%201939%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Tridip.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahi%20passed%20away%20at%20an%20early%20age.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20his%20legacy%20lives%20on%20in%20the%20landscape%20of%20Kaziranga%2C%20a%20dream%20he%20channelled%20all%20his%20efforts%20into.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froundglasssustain.com%2Fheroes%2Fmahi-miri%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMahi%20Miri%3A%20The%20Forgotten%20Hero%20Behind%20Kaziranga%3A%20%3C%2Fa%3Eby%20Bikash%20Bhattacharya%2C%20Published%20on%2030%20August%202024.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmishingrenaissance.blogspot.com%2F2008%2F11%2Fman-behind-kaziranga-national-parkmahi.html%3Fm%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Man%20Behind%20Kaziranga%20National%20Park%3A%20Mahi%20Chandra%20Miri%20%5BGreat%20Mising%20Personality%5D%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20by%20Mishing%20Renaissance%2C%20Published%20on%2013%20November%202008.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaziranga-national-park.com%2Fkaziranga-history.shtml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHistory%20of%20Kaziranga%20National%20Park%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753702200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.t